  "prompt": "Which is the real photo of Shivaji Maharaj drawn byMir Muhammad?",
  "response": "The real photo or painting of Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj drawn by Mir Muhammad is an important historical reference, but it is important to note that there are no authentic photographs from that era, as photography was not invented until the 19th century. However, Mir Muhammad was a court painter during the time of Shivaji Maharaj, and he is believed to have created portraits based on descriptions and features of Shivaji from his time.\n\nThe most recognized depiction attributed to Mir Muhammad is the painting housed in the collection of the Raja Dinkar Kelkar Museum in Pune, India. This painting is often referred to as one of the best representations of Shivaji Maharaj based on traditional iconography and historical descriptions.\n\nWhen looking for images online, it is essential to verify the sources to ensure that they represent authentic historical art rather than modern reinterpretations or artistic liberties.",
